  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In \"Avengers: Age of Ultron,\" Thor's hammer, Mj\u00f6lnir, shakes when Captain America attempts to lift it during a scene where the Avengers are having a party. This moment is significant because it hints at Captain America's worthiness. According to the mythos established in the Marvel comics and films, Mj\u00f6lnir can only be lifted by those deemed \"worthy\" by its enchantment.\n\nThe shaking indicates that Captain America is indeed close to being worthy, as he possesses the noble qualities that Mj\u00f6lnir recognizes, but he ultimately does not lift it. This scene serves to showcase the bond between the characters as well as to hint at Captain America's character growth and moral integrity, laying the groundwork for his eventual ability to wield Mj\u00f6lnir in \"Avengers: Endgame.\" The moment is both humorous and profound, encapsulating the themes of heroism and worthiness central to Thor's legacy.",
